Sorry for missing this.

Using class unions to achieve flexibility in slots has a long usage
history. Consider for example classes like DataFrameOrNull etc.

I would advise to avoid making methods on these class unions. I could see a
few exceptions though, perhaps along the examples you mention. But it very
quickly ends up being that you need if() statements etc inside the method
on the class union.

Best,
Kasper

On Fri, Jan 10, 2025 at 7:17?PM Axel Klenk <axel.klenk at gmail.com> wrote:

> Hi Herv?, Kasper, Helena and all,
>
> and thanks a lot for your replies!
>
> First of all, if this is a bug in the methods package, I'd of course
